\subsection{Comprehensive TSS and TF-miRNA Annotation}
\label{sec:comprehensive-tss-and-tf-mirna-annotatio}


Application of the validated pipeline yielded comprehensive annotations across human and

mouse miRNomes. We identified 28,828 putative TSSs for 1,745 human miRNAs and 1,181

mouse miRNAs, representing substantial expansion over previous annotations. Integration with

TF ChIP-seq data enabled mapping of over 6 million tissue-specific TF-miRNA interactions.

These interactions span hundreds of transcription factors and reveal complex regulatory circuits

controlling miRNA expression. The tissue-specific nature of these annotations enables

investigation of context-dependent miRNA regulation across diverse biological conditions.


\subsection{miRStart 2.0 Database Features and Functionality}
\label{sec:mirstart-2-0-database-features-and-funct}

The miRStart 2.0 web database provides intuitive access to all generated annotations. The

genome browser interface displays TSS predictions as interactive tracks, with color-coding

indicating prediction confidence and tissue specificity. Users can overlay supporting evidence

from individual sequencing datasets to assess data quality. The TF-miRNA interaction module

presents regulatory networks as searchable tables and interactive network graphs. Conservation

tracks enable identification of evolutionarily constrained regulatory elements. Export

functionality supports downstream analysis in standard formats, and the comprehensive

documentation facilitates integration into research workflows.


